Former Proteas fats bowler Mfuneko Ngam has been named as the new assistant coach of the Warriors Cricket franchise JOHANNESBURG - Former Proteas fast bowler Mfuneko Ngam has been named as the new assistant coach of the Warriors cricket franchise. Ngam, who played three Test matches for South Africa between 2000 and 2001, will assist Rivash Gobind who has graduated to the head coach position since the departure of Malibongwe Maketa to the national set up late last year. The Middledrift-born Ngam has previously headed up the cricket academy at the University of Fort Hare in Alice while he has also been part of Cricket South Africaâ€™s talent identification programmes in the past.